[{:rule-id "rule-ai", :item {:feed-id "hn-frontpage", :item-id "https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48166275", :title "Show HN: Codiff, a local diff review tool", :link "https://github.com/nkzw-tech/codiff/releases", :published-at #inst "2026-05-17T05:30:14.000-00:00", :content "Nowadays I review a lot of code locally that was written by llms. I used to review my own code using git + delta. It started to feel limiting with the amount of code written by llms. When looking at a large diff on Friday I pointed an llm at diffs.com and trees.software and told it to build an app. It only took 16 minutes, is extremely fast for large diffs, beautiful and minimal. Today I polished it up and added all the features that I need. It has file filters, search, an llm walkthrough mode, and review comments that you can paste back into your llm. I will be using Codiff a lot, and can finally review the large diff from Friday that led me to build this If you like it, fork it! Comments URL: https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48166275 Points: 18 # Comments: 7"}, :excerpts [{:text "... review a lot of code locally that was written by llms. I used to review my own code using git + delta. It started to feel limiting with the amount of code written by llms. When looking at a large diff on Friday I pointed an llm at diffs.com and trees.software and told it to...", :matched-terms ["llm"], :source :content} {:text "... that I need. It has file filters, search, an llm walkthrough mode, and review comments that you can paste back into your llm. I will be using Codiff a lot, and can finally...", :matched-terms ["llm"], :source :content}]}]